Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment, and low total CO₂, which may indicate mild metabolic acidosis. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, raising concern for renal dysfunction and possible dehydration or metabolic disturbance. HbA1c is unexpectedly low, possibly due to analytical or clinical factors. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, metabolic status, and review of diabetes assessment.
